[[File:Shiragayama Kofun, funkyu.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Full view of the tumulus (front mound on the left, rear mound in the back right)}}]] '''Shiragayama Kofun''' (白髪山古墳) is a {{ill|keyhole-shaped tumulus|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Habikino, Osaka|ja|羽曳野市|12=draft|12=draft}}, Osaka Prefecture, Nishiura 6-chome. It is situated at the southwestern edge of the {{ill|Furuichi Kofun Cluster|ja|古市古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}}.
The actual burial individual is unknown, but the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|12=draft|12=draft}} designates it as "'''Kawachi Saka-no-Hara Mausoleum'''" (河内坂門原陵), attributed to {{ill|Emperor Seinei|ja|清寧天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview ==
[[File:070727 Shiragayama Kofun aerial.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Aerial view of Shiragayama Kofun}}{{Small|{{National Land Image Information}}.}}]] Shiragayama Kofun has a total length of 115 meters, with the front mound measuring 128 meters in width and 11 meters in height, and the rear mound having a diameter of 63 meters and a height of 10.5 meters. The tumulus is characterized by its disproportionately large front mound, approximately twice as wide as the rear mound.
The name of the tumulus is derived from Emperor Seinei, who is said to have been born with {{ill|white hair|ja|白髪|12=draft|12=draft}} and was named Shiraga Ōyamato Nekonomikoto (白髪大倭根子命) in the {{ill|Kojiki|ja|古事記|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Based on the characteristics of the fragments of cylindrical haniwa unearthed, the tumulus is estimated to have been constructed in the early 6th century.
The site is managed by the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|12=draft|12=draft}}, which designates it as the mausoleum of Emperor Seinei. A {{ill|Haisho|ja|拝所|lt=worship site|12=draft|12=draft}} is located outside the moat at the front mound's central area.
Additionally, it is hypothesized that the {{ill|Yatsugura Kofun|ja|八雷古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Yukuhashi, Fukuoka|ja|行橋市|12=draft|12=draft}} was constructed as a scaled-down version of Shiragayama Kofun.<ref>http://www.city.yukuhashi.fukuoka.jp/doc/2015121500016/ Yukuhashi City official website</ref>
<gallery> File:Shiragayama Kofun, haisho.jpg|{{ill|Emperor Seinei|ja|清寧天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} Kawachi Saka-no-Hara Mausoleum {{ill|Haisho|ja|拝所|lt=Worship Site|12=draft|12=draft}} </gallery>
